This paper proposes an unsupervised framework for learning a deep convolutional neural network for single view depth prediction. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as depth estimation and image reconstruction, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's approach involves generating an inverse warp of the target image using the predicted depth and known inter-view displacement, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and graphics (cs.GR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.GR.
